Transferred from Staffordshire to Worcestershire on 20.10.1844. 
    Abolished 1.4.1953 and added to the parish of Broome.
Created 1.4.1953 out of the parishes of Broom and Chaddesley Corbett.

Abolished 1.4.1933 and added to the parish of Churchill & 
    Blakedown.

Created 1.4.1933 out of the parishes of Hagley, Churchill and 
    Kidderminster Foreign. See also Table 2, note (c).

Transferred from Shropshire to Worcestershire on 30.9.1895. Abolished 
    1.4.1933 and divided between the parishes of Bewdley, Upper Arley and Kidderminster 
    Foreign.
Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the Wyre Forest unparished area.

Abolished 1.4.1928 and added to the parish of Stourport. 
    See also Table 2, note (b).

Created 1.4.1928 from the parishes of Lower Mitton and Upper Mitton. 
    See also Table 2, notes (e), (f) and (g).
Transferred from Staffordshire to Worcestershire on 30.9.1895.
Renamed 1.4.1974 to become the parish of Wolverley & Cookley.
Created 1.4.1901 out of the parish of Kidderminster Foreign.
